The course provides an overview of the peculiarities of the teacher's activity in the conditions of the multicultural learning environment and develops students' practical skills of improving their own multicultural competence and managing of the study process in a multicultural group.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce the specifics of the teacher's activity in the conditions of the multicultural learning environment as well as to analyze students' learning styles and communication norms which are connected with cultural differences. To provide the knowledge and skills which are necessary for teaching in a multilingual and multicultural group.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the subject a student: 1) knows the peculiarity of the teacher's activity in the multicultural learning environment; 2) reflects on his/her own activity as a teacher in a multicultural group (intercultural tolerance, universal human values, positive ethnical identity, etc.); 3) plan a learning activity for a multicultural group.
